    "He asked whether rank(M) is infinite for a general A, but it remains open.",
    "d Follows by Theorem 1.4 (= Theorem 4.1) and [JJ01, GJ06].",
    "of the Mordell-Weil group A(K) of A over K. Among the fields appearing in the table, Kummer-faithful fields are K g,m for any g and any m, k[σ] for almost all σ ∈ G e k with e ≥ 2 (actually with e ≥ 1; the freeness result is not known for e = 1), and any finite extension K of k. The algebraic closure and the real closure of k are not Kummer-faithful.",
    "Recently, Lowry [Low23, Theorem 1] determined the structure of A(K) when K is a real closed field.",
    "Another example of a non-Kummer-faithful field K is K = k(A(k) tor) for a fixed A; obviously A(K) contains a non-trivial divisible subgroup A(k) tor."
